          <h2>Why HVAC Maintenance Matters in Louisiana</h2>
          <p>Louisiana's climate is tough on HVAC systems. High humidity, long cooling seasons, and salty Gulf air all contribute to wear and tear. Regular maintenance by a qualified HVAC contractor:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Extends Equipment Life:</strong> Well-maintained systems last 15-20 years vs. 10-12 for neglected units</li>
            <li><strong>Reduces Energy Costs:</strong> Clean, tuned systems operate 15-25% more efficiently</li>
            <li><strong>Prevents Breakdowns:</strong> Most AC failures are preventable with regular maintenance</li>
            <li><strong>Maintains Warranty:</strong> Many manufacturers require annual maintenance for warranty coverage</li>
            <li><strong>Improves Air Quality:</strong> Clean filters and coils mean cleaner air for your family</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Indoor Air Quality Solutions</h2>
